==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Garnierite
<hw>Gar"ni*er*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after the
French geologist <etsep>Garnier</etsep>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>An amorphous mineral of apple-green color; a hydrous silicate of
nickel and magnesia. It is an important ore of nickel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Garnish</ent>⟦br⟧
